<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-11-0039 </DOCNO><TEXT>A summary is given of the discussion of the papers on the background toenergy problems presented at the Conference on the Economics of Choicebetween Energy Sources held by the International Economic Associationin Japan. Three broad topics are discussed: (1) whether the energy disturbancescontributed to the economic malaise of the 1970's and early 1980's, (2)the general nature of the policy response to energy shortages and (3)the presentation of economic analyses.</TEXT></DOC>